paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted information on the BRCA2 gene variant brca2Q658X, including penetrance data and individual records.

individual_records.evidence_sentence: Homozygous brca2 mutant zebrafish are viable but fail to develop ovaries and develop into infertile males with deficient spermatogenesis.

functional_data.summary: The brca2 mutant zebrafish line sheds light on the role of brca2 in ovary development and tumorigenesis in reproductive organs.

variants.segregation_data: Yes, it segregates with disease in the context of the study.
variants.additional_notes: The brca2Q658X variant is similar to BRCA2 mutations found in humans with hereditary breast and ovarian cancers.
key_quotes: Homozygous brca2 mutant zebrafish are viable but fail to develop ovaries and develop into infertile males with deficient spermatogenesis.
Furthermore, brca2 mutant zebrafish are predisposed to testicular neoplasia, while tumorigenesis is enhanced in a tp53 deficient genetic background.

extraction_metadata.notes: The extraction was straightforward as the relevant data was clearly presented in the text.
